I think Bevy is too cool for me. The people who work here are downright cool. I sound like such a dork saying that, but I love their vibe! I feel like I've entered a new world when I'm in here. I feel like I'm in Brooklyn? Maybe? Somewhere groovy, haha. I love the decor, which you would never assume it has when you see it outside. I've really never found it super appealing or alluring, if I'm being honest. I was looking up happy hour options when it came up, and I figured I'd try it out because it's stuck around Kakaako for SO LONG that I felt it should be given a fair shot. I really did enjoy it. The drinks are creative, as they have a ton of options for you to choose from. I would come back just to try out a few more! The food is interesting. Pricey, I'd say, but I really enjoyed what I got (and shared) with a friend. Calamari. YUM. Amazing, highly recommend. There's just something about it. Also, the mushroom risotto with duck was surprisingly so delicious. I've only recently become a risotto lover, and this did not disappoint. I don't often eat duck and though I wouldn't say it's my favorite meat, it went really well with this dish surprisingly! I heard they have taco tuesday.. So I think I might give that one a shot next! Will for sure be back at some point. I see why they've stuck around. Seems like they have a super loyal following. Love that!

The cocktails and apps here are all freaking delicious. The only thing I wasn't crazy about were the grilled peppers (nothing special) and the calamari (wayyy to salty - though my boyfriend loved those) but everything else we tried was amazing. It was kind of pricey but not overpriced for the quality. The "mai-thai"s don't totally taste like mai-tais (to me) but are super tasty and worth getting. The hygge and caipirinhas are also top notch.

One of many dining options at the SALT complex in Kaka’ako, Bevy offers a great happy hour menu that ranges beyond your standard pub fare. The large shrimp on lemongrass skewers were tender, the crisped jalapeños popped on the fried calamari and we could have eaten the fried macaroni balls for days. Elote was a surprising find on the menu, as was the duck on a heavenly mushroom risotto (on the dinner menu).  After tromping around Kaka’ako to view the new POW! WOW! murals, Bevy was the perfect way to end the evening.

With all the yelp reviews and buzz surrounding "Bevy", my gf and I finally gave it a shot after weeks of anticipation and excitement. I hate to say it but we were very disappointed! The only good thing we would come back for, if we ever decide to would be their $1.50/oyster and $3.50 Bikini Blondes during their Happy Hour from 4-7pm. Other than that, parking was difficult to find, ambiance was trendy but dimmed and uncomfortable, service was unwelcoming and food portions were small and not worth the cost. Also, their menu is too "fluffy" with description of their food. It's really not that hard in making simple items taste good but they found a way to make it difficult and complicated. It's like putting make up on a pig and calling it "Kobe prime rib".
